p.q:
That for the purposes of any Act resulting from the Courts and Legal Services Bill [Lords], it is expedient to authorise—


(a) the payment out of money provided by Parliament of—


(i) any sums required by the Lord Chancellor for the payment of grants under the Act to the Advisory Committee on Legal Education and Conduct and the Authorised Conveyancing Practitioners Board;

(ii) any other expenses incurred by the Lord Chancellor under the Act; and

(iii) any increase attributable to the Act in the sums payable out of money provided by Parliament under any other enactment;


(b) the payment out of the Consolidated Fund of any increase attributable to the Act in the sums to be paid out of that Fund under any other enactment. —[Mr. Lilley.]
